00:00:35.040 --> 00:00:45.200
everything. Sport, education, he had an extreme thirst for knowledge. Books, surrounded himself

00:00:45.200 --> 00:00:54.240
with books and being the eldest of a family where their father had died when they were quite young,

00:00:54.240 --> 00:01:01.120
he became the breadwinner. He spent very little of his childhood in his mother's house. He was

00:01:01.120 --> 00:01:10.800
living with his uncle who lived 13 miles away from the family home. So my dad had a 13 mile cycle trip

00:01:10.800 --> 00:01:19.360
to school every day. He won what was called an open scholarship to attend the Royal College in Cupid,

00:01:19.440 --> 00:01:26.000
which was a fee-paying school but he won an open scholarship. He came from quite a poor background

00:01:26.000 --> 00:01:32.480
as you can imagine but he was the highest scoring pupil on the whole of the island.

00:01:33.040 --> 00:01:38.480
So he won this scholarship to go to the school. Whilst he was a pupil there, he was very

00:01:38.480 --> 00:01:45.840
entrepreneurial and started giving private lessons to boys and girls who quite didn't reach the

00:01:45.840 --> 00:01:48.960
expectation that they were supposed to but had a bit of money.

00:01:49.680 --> 00:01:57.520
